    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 45899.0,
      "end_time": 48899.0,
      "text": "So the Aztecs weren’t the first impressive polity in Mesoamerica,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 48899.0,
      "end_time": 51139.0,
      "text": "that honor would go to the Olmecs or the Mayans."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 51139.0,
      "end_time": 52789.0,
      "text": "But they were probably the greatest."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 52789.0,
      "end_time": 56559.0,
      "text": "The Aztecs formed out of an alliance of three major cities in modern day Mexico in about"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 56559.0,
      "end_time": 57690.0,
      "text": "1430,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 57690.0,
      "end_time": 61039.0,
      "text": "just 89 years before Cortez and his conquistadors showed up."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 61039.0,
      "end_time": 62719.0,
      "text": "The Aztec state was very hierarchical,"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 62719.0,
      "end_time": 66100.0,
      "text": "with an emperor at the top and a group unruly nobles beneath him."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 66100.0,
      "end_time": 66439.0,
      "text": "Just like Europe."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 66439.0,
      "end_time": 67130.0,
      "text": "And in addition,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 67130.0,
      "end_time": 71119.0,
      "text": "there was a class of powerful priests whose job it was to keep order in the cosmos."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 71119.0,
      "end_time": 71740.0,
      "text": "[like in the 5th Element?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 71740.0,
      "end_time": 75680.0,
      "text": "So, Aztec religion held that history was cyclical and punctuated by terrible disasters and then"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 75680.0,
      "end_time": 77509.0,
      "text": "would ultimately end with a massive apocalypse."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 77509.0,
      "end_time": 80250.0,
      "text": "And the job of the priests was to avoid these disasters,"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 80250.0,
      "end_time": 81490.0,
      "text": "by appeasing the gods,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 81490.0,
      "end_time": 83340.0,
      "text": "generally through human sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 83340.0,
      "end_time": 86170.0,
      "text": "The Aztecs extended their control over most of southern Mexico,"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 86170.0,
      "end_time": 87729.0,
      "text": "parts of Guatemala and the Yucatan."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 87729.0,
      "end_time": 89789.0,
      "text": "And they demanded tribute from conquered people in the form of"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 89789.0,
      "end_time": 92679.0,
      "text": "goods, precious metals, and people to sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 92679.0,
      "end_time": 94189.0,
      "text": "If you’re familiar with The Hunger Games,"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 94189.0,
      "end_time": 94979.0,
      "text": "[You are totally familiar with the Hunger Games...]"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 94979.0,
      "end_time": 97880.0,
      "text": "it won’t surprise you to learn that this didn’t sit very well with said conquered"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 97880.0,
      "end_time": 98429.0,
      "text": "people."
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 98429.0,
      "end_time": 101539.0,
      "text": "And the fact that the Aztecs were basically ruling over thousands of people who hated"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 101539.0,
      "end_time": 105909.0,
      "text": "them made it a lot easier for Cortez to come in and find allies to overthrow them."
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 105909.0,
      "end_time": 106439.0,
      "text": "All that noted,"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 106439.0,
      "end_time": 107280.0,
      "text": "in less than a hundred years,"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 107280.0,
      "end_time": 109450.0,
      "text": "the Aztecs accomplished some amazing things."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 109450.0,
      "end_time": 112289.0,
      "text": "Especially the building of their capital city Tenochtitlan,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 112289.0,
      "end_time": 114090.0,
      "text": "on the site of modern day Mexico City,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 114090.0,
      "end_time": 117240.0,
      "text": "which was like Venice in that it was divided and serviced by canals."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 117240.0,
      "end_time": 119509.0,
      "text": "They also had floating gardens, called chinampas,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 119509.0,
      "end_time": 120969.0,
      "text": "which provided food for the city."
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 120969.0,
      "end_time": 121109.0,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 121109.0,
      "end_time": 122229.0,
      "text": "it’s already time for the open letter?"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 122229.0,
      "end_time": 122579.0,
      "text": "Alright."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 122579.0,
      "end_time": 126380.0,
      "text": "[Switches from chair to lemon/lime velvet throne of impending structural disaster]"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 126380.0,
      "end_time": 127889.0,
      "text": "An open letter to Human Sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 127889.0,
      "end_time": 128340.0,
      "text": "But first,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 128340.0,
      "end_time": 130530.0,
      "text": "let’s see what’s in the secret compartment today."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 130530.0,
      "end_time": 131360.0,
      "text": "Oh, nice."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 131360.0,
      "end_time": 132190.0,
      "text": "Come on."
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 132190.0,
      "end_time": 133690.0,
      "text": "Be a mushroom, be a mushroom, be a---"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 133690.0,
      "end_time": 135360.0,
      "text": "oh dahh."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 135360.0,
      "end_time": 136190.0,
      "text": "Dear human sacrifice,"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 136190.0,
      "end_time": 136629.0,
      "text": "look,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 136629.0,
      "end_time": 138440.0,
      "text": "I’m not going to defend you."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 138440.0,
      "end_time": 142870.0,
      "text": "But if you really believe that the world is going to end if the gods are not appeased,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 142870.0,
      "end_time": 145540.0,
      "text": "then human sacrifice kind of makes sense."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 145540.0,
      "end_time": 146099.0,
      "text": "[But not if you’re Willie in Temple of Doom...]"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 146099.0,
      "end_time": 147150.0,
      "text": "And as evidence for this,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 147150.0,
      "end_time": 147849.0,
      "text": "let me submit to you"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 147849.0,
      "end_time": 150890.0,
      "text": "that we engage in human sacrifice all the time."
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 150890.0,
      "end_time": 152480.0,
      "text": "Remember the movie, The Dirty Dozen?"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 152480.0,
      "end_time": 153069.0,
      "text": "No?"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 153069.0,
      "end_time": 154069.0,
      "text": "Because you’re too young?"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 154069.0,
      "end_time": 154689.0,
      "text": "That makes me hate myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 154689.0,
      "end_time": 155299.0,
      "text": "[Don’t worry, Johnny Bookwriter, “vintage” will always be cool.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 155299.0,
      "end_time": 158760.0,
      "text": "Anyway, it was all about glorious sacrifice and how a few have to die in order for many"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 158760.0,
      "end_time": 159019.0,
      "text": "to live."
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 159019.0,
      "end_time": 160720.0,
      "text": "Did you at least see that-- that uh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 160720.0,
      "end_time": 162370.0,
      "text": "meteor movie that Ben Affleck was in?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 162370.0,
      "end_time": 163610.0,
      "text": "What was that called, Stan?"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 163610.0,
      "end_time": 165250.0,
      "text": "Asteroid. [Stan, off camera]"
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 165250.0,
      "end_time": 165659.0,
      "text": "Asteroid!"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 165659.0,
      "end_time": 167299.0,
      "text": "Armageddon. [Stan, off camera]"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 167299.0,
      "end_time": 167709.0,
      "text": "Armageddon!"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 167709.0,
      "end_time": 168120.0,
      "text": "Armageddon."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 168120.0,
      "end_time": 169650.0,
      "text": "Right. Like that..."
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 169650.0,
      "end_time": 170670.0,
      "text": "Human sacrifice."
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 170670.0,
      "end_time": 172150.0,
      "text": "Best wishes, John Green."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 172150.0,
      "end_time": 172379.0,
      "text": "Alright,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 172379.0,
      "end_time": 175349.0,
      "text": "now let’s head south to the Inca civilization, which was older than"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 175349.0,
      "end_time": 177510.0,
      "text": "the Aztecs and in some ways even more impressive."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 177510.0,
      "end_time": 178459.0,
      "text": "Founded in the 13th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 178459.0,
      "end_time": 183260.0,
      "text": "the Inca empire ruled between 4 and 6 million people by the time the Spanish showed up in"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 183260.0,
      "end_time": 183840.0,
      "text": "1532."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 183840.0,
      "end_time": 186420.0,
      "text": "Trade and a very effective administrative structure held the empire together, which"
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 186420.0,
      "end_time": 190299.0,
      "text": "was even more impressive when you consider all the roads and temples that were built"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 190299.0,
      "end_time": 193370.0,
      "text": "atop mountains with nothing to haul things up those mountains,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 193370.0,
      "end_time": 195280.0,
      "text": "except for llamas and people."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 195280.0,
      "end_time": 195629.0,
      "text": "[Thought the Mongols were the exception?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 195629.0,
      "end_time": 198950.0,
      "text": "The Inca had no written language but they were able to keep records with knotted strings"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 198950.0,
      "end_time": 204950.0,
      "text": "called quipus. [Gesundheit!]"
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 204950.0,
      "end_time": 208670.0,
      "text": "And vitally, they ordered every male peasant under the Inca control to do unpaid work for"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 208670.0,
      "end_time": 211640.0,
      "text": "the Inca government for a specified period of time each year."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 211640.0,
      "end_time": 212090.0,
      "text": "This system,"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 212090.0,
      "end_time": 213269.0,
      "text": "which the Inca called mit’a"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 213269.0,
      "end_time": 215500.0,
      "text": "allowed them to build all those roads and temples."
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 215500.0,
      "end_time": 218890.0,
      "text": "The Spanish would later adopt this system, and the hierarchical system with the emperor"
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 218890.0,
      "end_time": 220819.0,
      "text": "at the top, except they would make it all,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 220819.0,
      "end_time": 221170.0,
      "text": "you know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 221170.0,
      "end_time": 222260.0,
      "text": "much suckier. [Is that a historical term?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 222260.0,
      "end_time": 222500.0,
      "text": "And, yes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 222500.0,
      "end_time": 224110.0,
      "text": "that is a technical historian term."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 224110.0,
      "end_time": 228969.0,
      "text": "So, the Spanish arrived in Mexico in 1519, and in Peru in 1532, benefiting in both cases"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 228969.0,
      "end_time": 231099.0,
      "text": "from total chaos due to disease."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 231099.0,
      "end_time": 234939.0,
      "text": "And after conquering the Incas and the Aztecs, they created an empire with two administrative"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 234939.0,
      "end_time": 235189.0,
      "text": "divisions."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 235189.0,
      "end_time": 238459.0,
      "text": "The Viceroyalty of New Spain, founded in 1521,"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 238459.0,
      "end_time": 241549.0,
      "text": "and the Viceroyalty of Peru, founded in 1542."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 241549.0,
      "end_time": 241939.0,
      "text": "In some ways,"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 241939.0,
      "end_time": 244730.0,
      "text": "the Aztec and Inca empires were perfect for Spanish conquest."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 244730.0,
      "end_time": 246439.0,
      "text": "Their administrative structures were similar,"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 246439.0,
      "end_time": 249170.0,
      "text": "there was a similar link between secular and religious power,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 249170.0,
      "end_time": 250739.0,
      "text": "albeit different religions."
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 250739.0,
      "end_time": 254299.0,
      "text": "All of which made it relatively easy for the Spanish crown to step into the void left by"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 254299.0,
      "end_time": 257760.0,
      "text": "those two great empires and send their own administrators to run the place."
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 257760.0,
      "end_time": 261150.0,
      "text": "While most of the Spanish aristocrats who came over ran large agricultural operations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 261149.99999999997,
      "end_time": 263310.0,
      "text": "you don’t see a lot of movies called, like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 263310.0,
      "end_time": 265840.0,
      "text": "Indiana Jones and the Search for A Nice Farm in the Countryside."
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 265840.0,
      "end_time": 266500.0,
      "text": "[Probably still much better than that Crystal Skull nonsense.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 266500.0,
      "end_time": 268790.0,
      "text": "The real glory for conquistadors was gold."
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 268790.0,
      "end_time": 269820.0,
      "text": "Initially they found some,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 269820.0,
      "end_time": 271370.0,
      "text": "both in the Caribbean and in Mexico,"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 271370.0,
      "end_time": 272530.0,
      "text": "but never enough to get,"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 272530.0,
      "end_time": 273280.0,
      "text": "like, super-rich."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 273280.0,
      "end_time": 274250.0,
      "text": "Fortunately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 274250.0,
      "end_time": 275570.0,
      "text": "or as I will argue, unfortunately,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 275570.0,
      "end_time": 278120.0,
      "text": "they did find a mountain made of silver."
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 278120.0,
      "end_time": 279600.0,
      "text": "So the Spanish adapted the mita,"
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 279600.0,
      "end_time": 282090.0,
      "text": "which the Incas had used to build roads and public buildings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 282090.0,
      "end_time": 284060.0,
      "text": "to mine and process that silver."
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 284060.0,
      "end_time": 288580.0,
      "text": "So 1/7th of the adult male Indian population from each district was required to work in"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 288580.0,
      "end_time": 289960.0,
      "text": "the silver mines for a year,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 289960.0,
      "end_time": 291690.0,
      "text": "being paid only subsistence wages."
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 291690.0,
      "end_time": 295310.0,
      "text": "Now, you might wonder why the Spanish didn’t purchase African slaves to work in the mines."
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 295310.0,
      "end_time": 296560.0,
      "text": "They did in Mexico,"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 296560.0,
      "end_time": 299750.0,
      "text": "but in South America it was cheaper to use indigenous labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 299750.0,
      "end_time": 301400.0,
      "text": "Purchasing slaves was inefficient because"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 301400.0,
      "end_time": 303160.0,
      "text": "1. They didn’t have experience working at high"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 303160.0,
      "end_time": 303760.0,
      "text": "altitudes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 303760.0,
      "end_time": 306130.0,
      "text": "and 2. Mine work was super deadly."
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 306130.0,
      "end_time": 306580.0,
      "text": "Mercury,"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 306580.0,
      "end_time": 308170.0,
      "text": "which can be used to refine silver ore,"
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 308170.0,
      "end_time": 310190.0,
      "text": "was found at the mountain of Huancavelica."
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 310190.0,
      "end_time": 314270.0,
      "text": "And mercury poisoning among miners was so common that parents would often maim their"
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 314270.0,
      "end_time": 317140.0,
      "text": "children to keep them from having to work the mines."
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 317140.0,
      "end_time": 319570.0,
      "text": "You can see why I’m struggling to be festive!"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 319570.0,
      "end_time": 320650.0,
      "text": "Let’s go to the Thought Bubble."
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 320650.0,
      "end_time": 321290.0,
      "text": "[Let’s go see if the Canadians can zazz things up a bit...]"
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 321290.0,
      "end_time": 326690.0,
      "text": "So Spanish mines in the Americas produced over 150,000 tons of silver between the 16th"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 326690.0,
      "end_time": 330410.0,
      "text": "and the 18th centuries, over 80% of the world’s supply."
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 330410.0,
      "end_time": 334510.0,
      "text": "Spain became the richest nation in Europe and Spanish silver pesos became the de-facto"
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 334510.0,
      "end_time": 335160.0,
      "text": "currency."
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 335160.0,
      "end_time": 336090.0,
      "text": "But the Spanish royal family"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 336090.0,
      "end_time": 338270.0,
      "text": "does not appear to have understood inflation—"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 338270.0,
      "end_time": 342710.0,
      "text": "and the huge influx of silver caused skyrocketing inflation, and since they never set tax rates"
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 342710.0,
      "end_time": 347120.0,
      "text": "to account for it, they collected the same amount of money sixty years after the discovery"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 347120.0,
      "end_time": 351490.0,
      "text": "of silver, but that money was worth a fraction of what it once had been."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 351490.0,
      "end_time": 352000.0,
      "text": "And in general,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 352000.0,
      "end_time": 355660.0,
      "text": "it’s not clear that Spain benefited much from the discovery of silver."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 355660.0,
      "end_time": 359930.0,
      "text": "Rich countries have a way of finding their way into expensive and not totally necessary"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 359930.0,
      "end_time": 364380.0,
      "text": "wars, and Spain was no exception. While empire wasn’t the central cause of Spain’s many"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 364380.0,
      "end_time": 365500.0,
      "text": "16th century wars,"
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 365500.0,
      "end_time": 367340.0,
      "text": "it sure did fund them."
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 367340.0,
      "end_time": 368050.0,
      "text": "So in 1519"
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 368050.0,
      "end_time": 370120.0,
      "text": "(which was a heck of a year for Spain)"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 370120.0,
      "end_time": 375220.0,
      "text": "Charles V united the kingdoms of Spain and Austria by being named head of the Holy Roman"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 375220.0,
      "end_time": 375870.0,
      "text": "Empire,"
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 375870.0,
      "end_time": 376600.0,
      "text": "so called because"
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 376600.0,
      "end_time": 378020.0,
      "text": "it was not Holy,"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 378020.0,
      "end_time": 378940.0,
      "text": "not Roman,"
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 378940.0,
      "end_time": 379940.0,
      "text": "and not an Empire."
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 379940.0,
      "end_time": 383520.0,
      "text": "Charles had this dream of a unified central Europe, which was constantly being thwarted"
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 383520.0,
      "end_time": 388300.0,
      "text": "by German nobles, who had a dream of a non-unified central Europe, and eventually Charles V’s"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 388300.0,
      "end_time": 393160.0,
      "text": "ambitions were shattered and he gave the Austrian half of his kingdom to his son Ferdinand and"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 393160.0,
      "end_time": 396650.0,
      "text": "gave Spain with the American stuff to Philip in 1556."
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 396650.0,
      "end_time": 397710.0,
      "text": "Thanks, Thought Bubble."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 397710.0,
      "end_time": 401590.0,
      "text": "So, Philip II didn’t only inherited all of Spain’s holdings in the Americas and"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 401590.0,
      "end_time": 402770.0,
      "text": "in Europe and in the"
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 402770.0,
      "end_time": 404600.0,
      "text": "Phillip-not-a-coincidence-ines. [Dedicated to that reach, eh?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 404600.0,
      "end_time": 406710.0,
      "text": "He also inherited a rebellion in the Netherlands,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 406710.0,
      "end_time": 407530.0,
      "text": "because the Dutch were like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 407530.0,
      "end_time": 410720.0,
      "text": "“We’re gonna be Protestant, also you guys know nothing about economics,”"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 410720.0,
      "end_time": 411460.0,
      "text": "which, incidentally,"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 411460.0,
      "end_time": 413000.0,
      "text": "the Dutch are still saying to the Spanish."
    },
    {
      "index": 211,
      "start_time": 413000.0,
      "end_time": 416590.0,
      "text": "And then the English sided with the Dutch and there was a war featuring a disastrous"
    },
    {
      "index": 212,
      "start_time": 416590.0,
      "end_time": 417770.0,
      "text": "invasion of England,"
    },
    {
      "index": 213,
      "start_time": 417770.0,
      "end_time": 418990.0,
      "text": "called the Spanish Armada,"
    },
    {
      "index": 214,
      "start_time": 418990.0,
      "end_time": 419700.0,
      "text": "in 1588."
    },
    {
      "index": 215,
      "start_time": 419700.0,
      "end_time": 423000.0,
      "text": "England’s success against the Spanish, even though it can largely be chalked up to the"
    },
    {
      "index": 216,
      "start_time": 423000.0,
      "end_time": 423150.0,
      "text": "weather,"
    },
    {
      "index": 217,
      "start_time": 423150.0,
      "end_time": 425550.0,
      "text": "was credited to queen Elizabeth I. [Like a boss, even still.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 218,
      "start_time": 425550.0,
      "end_time": 428520.0,
      "text": "That led to a period of wealth and national pride, which meant that people had both the"
    },
    {
      "index": 219,
      "start_time": 428520.0,
      "end_time": 430230.0,
      "text": "money and the desire to see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 220,
      "start_time": 430230.0,
      "end_time": 430890.0,
      "text": "I don’t know,"
    },
    {
      "index": 221,
      "start_time": 430890.0,
      "end_time": 433610.0,
      "text": "plays about old English Kings named Richard."
    },
    {
      "index": 222,
      "start_time": 433610.0,
      "end_time": 434760.0,
      "text": "And that, my friends,"
    },
    {
      "index": 223,
      "start_time": 434760.0,
      "end_time": 438790.0,
      "text": "is how the discovery of silver in Bolivia contributed to the genius of William Shakespeare."
    },
    {
      "index": 224,
      "start_time": 438790.0,
      "end_time": 439510.0,
      "text": "[And Kevin Bacon?]"
    },
    {
      "index": 225,
      "start_time": 439510.0,
      "end_time": 439740.0,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "index": 226,
      "start_time": 439740.0,
      "end_time": 441360.0,
      "text": "American silver didn’t cause these wars"
    },
    {
      "index": 227,
      "start_time": 441360.0,
      "end_time": 443080.0,
      "text": "anymore than it wrote Hamlet,"
    },
    {
      "index": 228,
      "start_time": 443080.0,
      "end_time": 445400.0,
      "text": "but the new wealth made both more possible."
    },
    {
      "index": 229,
      "start_time": 445400.0,
      "end_time": 448900.0,
      "text": "Knowing that they had this enormous silver “war chest” at their disposal made them"
    },
    {
      "index": 230,
      "start_time": 448900.0,
      "end_time": 452910.0,
      "text": "much more inclined to build all those ships that got sunk in 1588."
    },
    {
      "index": 231,
      "start_time": 452910.0,
      "end_time": 456030.0,
      "text": "And soon enough even a mountain of silver could not pay for all the warring, and the"
    },
    {
      "index": 232,
      "start_time": 456030.0,
      "end_time": 459560.0,
      "text": "Spanish crown had to borrow money, which they couldn’t pay back, so they defaulted on"
    },
    {
      "index": 233,
      "start_time": 459560.0,
      "end_time": 461860.0,
      "text": "their debt several times in the 17th century."
    },
    {
      "index": 234,
      "start_time": 461860.0,
      "end_time": 462870.0,
      "text": "Yay, silver."
    },
    {
      "index": 235,
      "start_time": 462870.0,
      "end_time": 463370.0,
      "text": "So,"
    },
    {
      "index": 236,
      "start_time": 463370.0,
      "end_time": 465370.0,
      "text": "most of the silver mined in the Americas went to Europe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 237,
      "start_time": 465370.0,
      "end_time": 467380.0,
      "text": "but at least a third of it went to China."
    },
    {
      "index": 238,
      "start_time": 467380.0,
      "end_time": 468020.0,
      "text": "Either directly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 239,
      "start_time": 468020.0,
      "end_time": 469000.0,
      "text": "on Spanish galleons,"
    },
    {
      "index": 240,
      "start_time": 469000.0,
      "end_time": 471390.0,
      "text": "or indirectly through through the purchase of Chinese goods."
    },
    {
      "index": 241,
      "start_time": 471390.0,
      "end_time": 474400.0,
      "text": "China had encountered inflation of its own after printing the world’s first paper money"
    },
    {
      "index": 242,
      "start_time": 474400.0,
      "end_time": 475250.0,
      "text": "in the 12th century,"
    },
    {
      "index": 243,
      "start_time": 475250.0,
      "end_time": 476900.0,
      "text": "so they switched back to coins."
    },
    {
      "index": 244,
      "start_time": 476900.0,
      "end_time": 477530.0,
      "text": "Initially,"
    },
    {
      "index": 245,
      "start_time": 477530.0,
      "end_time": 479440.0,
      "text": "Chinese coins were made out of copper or bronze,"
    },
    {
      "index": 246,
      "start_time": 479440.0,
      "end_time": 481550.0,
      "text": "but their economy was so big—"
    },
    {
      "index": 247,
      "start_time": 481550.0,
      "end_time": 484720.0,
      "text": "they were the leading producer of consumer goods until the 19th century—"
    },
    {
      "index": 248,
      "start_time": 484720.0,
      "end_time": 485620.0,
      "text": "that they ran out."
    },
    {
      "index": 249,
      "start_time": 485620.0,
      "end_time": 486450.0,
      "text": "So they went to silver."
    },
    {
      "index": 250,
      "start_time": 486450.0,
      "end_time": 488010.0,
      "text": "Now, China didn’t have a lot of silver itself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 251,
      "start_time": 488010.0,
      "end_time": 489250.0,
      "text": "but Japan did,"
    },
    {
      "index": 252,
      "start_time": 489250.0,
      "end_time": 491080.0,
      "text": "so they traded manufactured goods for it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 253,
      "start_time": 491080.0,
      "end_time": 492650.0,
      "text": "but soon even that wasn’t enough."
    },
    {
      "index": 254,
      "start_time": 492650.0,
      "end_time": 496780.0,
      "text": "This was mostly because in the 16th century, China changed its tax structure."
    },
    {
      "index": 255,
      "start_time": 496780.0,
      "end_time": 497520.0,
      "text": "Taxes, man,"
    },
    {
      "index": 256,
      "start_time": 497520.0,
      "end_time": 499810.0,
      "text": "they’re at the center of human history. [Progress doesn’t fund itself, yo.]"
    },
    {
      "index": 257,
      "start_time": 499810.0,
      "end_time": 504020.0,
      "text": "In the early part of the Ming Dynasty, Chinese farmers paid their taxes in goods, mainly"
    },
    {
      "index": 258,
      "start_time": 504020.0,
      "end_time": 504990.0,
      "text": "grain, and labor."
    },
    {
      "index": 259,
      "start_time": 504990.0,
      "end_time": 508900.0,
      "text": "But as more silver entered the economy, the Ming government changed its policy and required"
    },
    {
      "index": 260,
      "start_time": 508900.0,
      "end_time": 510880.0,
      "text": "taxes to be paid in silver."
    },
    {
      "index": 261,
      "start_time": 510880.0,
      "end_time": 514569.0,
      "text": "This meant that almost everyone in China had to produce something that could be sold for"
    },
    {
      "index": 262,
      "start_time": 514568.99999999994,
      "end_time": 514938.99999999994,
      "text": "silver,"
    },
    {
      "index": 263,
      "start_time": 514938.99999999994,
      "end_time": 516338.99999999994,
      "text": "which usually meant silk."
    },
    {
      "index": 264,
      "start_time": 516339.00000000006,
      "end_time": 516639.00000000006,
      "text": "In fact,"
    },
    {
      "index": 265,
      "start_time": 516639.0,
      "end_time": 519099.0,
      "text": "the Ming government often required people to make silk."
    },
    {
      "index": 266,
      "start_time": 519099.00000000006,
      "end_time": 522719.00000000006,
      "text": "That glut of silk inevitably led to a price drop, which hurt the Chinese economy but not"
    },
    {
      "index": 267,
      "start_time": 522719.00000000006,
      "end_time": 527040.0,
      "text": "nearly as much as it hurt the Spanish economy, where almost every silk producer was put out"
    },
    {
      "index": 268,
      "start_time": 527040.0,
      "end_time": 527920.0,
      "text": "of business."
    },
    {
      "index": 269,
      "start_time": 527920.0,
      "end_time": 530300.0,
      "text": "So much for the idea that global outsourcing is a new problem."
    },
    {
      "index": 270,
      "start_time": 530300.0,
      "end_time": 533079.0,
      "text": "You’d think all this silver would make the Chinese incredibly rich,"
    },
    {
      "index": 271,
      "start_time": 533079.0,
      "end_time": 534139.0,
      "text": "just like the Spanish, right?"
    },
    {
      "index": 272,
      "start_time": 534139.0,
      "end_time": 537290.0,
      "text": "Well, yes, just like the Spanish, in that they got rich,"
    },
    {
      "index": 273,
      "start_time": 537290.0,
      "end_time": 538649.0,
      "text": "they didn’t stay rich."
    },
    {
      "index": 274,
      "start_time": 538649.0,
      "end_time": 541290.0,
      "text": "The Ming government also failed to peg taxes to inflation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 275,
      "start_time": 541290.0,
      "end_time": 542620.0,
      "text": "and spent too much on defense,"
    },
    {
      "index": 276,
      "start_time": 542620.0,
      "end_time": 543730.0,
      "text": "notably on the Great Wall."
    },
    {
      "index": 277,
      "start_time": 543730.0,
      "end_time": 546329.0,
      "text": "And by the 17th century the Ming were overthrown by the Fu Manchus."
    },
    {
      "index": 278,
      "start_time": 546329.0,
      "end_time": 546589.0,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "index": 279,
      "start_time": 546589.0,
      "end_time": 547680.0,
      "text": "it’s just the Manchus?"
    },
    {
      "index": 280,
      "start_time": 547680.0,
      "end_time": 548100.0,
      "text": "Gah."
    },
    {
      "index": 281,
      "start_time": 548100.0,
      "end_time": 549769.0,
      "text": "History, always disappointing me."
    },
    {
      "index": 282,
      "start_time": 549769.0,
      "end_time": 551290.0,
      "text": "As the historian Dennis Flynn put it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 283,
      "start_time": 551290.0,
      "end_time": 555529.0,
      "text": "“A significant hunk of the GDP of China – then the world’s biggest economy – was"
    },
    {
      "index": 284,
      "start_time": 555529.0,
      "end_time": 560199.0,
      "text": "surrendered in order to secure a white metal that was produced mostly in Spanish America"
    },
    {
      "index": 285,
      "start_time": 560199.0,
      "end_time": 561050.0,
      "text": "and Japan."
    },
    {
      "index": 286,
      "start_time": 561050.0,
      "end_time": 564220.0,
      "text": "…Think about what else those resources could have been used for.” #"
    },
    {
      "index": 287,
      "start_time": 564220.0,
      "end_time": 567490.0,
      "text": "The Spanish empire’s silver trade was the first truly global market—"
    },
    {
      "index": 288,
      "start_time": 567490.0,
      "end_time": 568399.0,
      "text": "even India was involved,"
    },
    {
      "index": 289,
      "start_time": 568399.0,
      "end_time": 569889.0,
      "text": "but we’re really out of time—"
    },
    {
      "index": 290,
      "start_time": 569889.0,
      "end_time": 571560.0,
      "text": "and its consequences are dire,"
    },
    {
      "index": 291,
      "start_time": 571560.0,
      "end_time": 573329.0,
      "text": "even if it did make some people rich."
    },
    {
      "index": 292,
      "start_time": 573329.0,
      "end_time": 576550.0,
      "text": "Both Spain and China experienced inflation that weakened their governments."
    },
    {
      "index": 293,
      "start_time": 576550.0,
      "end_time": 577670.0,
      "text": "The environment suffered."
    },
    {
      "index": 294,
      "start_time": 577670.0,
      "end_time": 581750.0,
      "text": "The search for precious metals led the Spanish to find and eventually destroy two of the"
    },
    {
      "index": 295,
      "start_time": 581750.0,
      "end_time": 583220.0,
      "text": "world’s great empires,"
    },
    {
      "index": 296,
      "start_time": 583220.0,
      "end_time": 584480.0,
      "text": "the Aztecs and the Inca."
    },
    {
      "index": 297,
      "start_time": 584480.0,
      "end_time": 588410.0,
      "text": "And many thousands were killed mining silver and the mercury used to refine it."
    },
    {
      "index": 298,
      "start_time": 588410.0,
      "end_time": 590329.0,
      "text": "But before you say it wasn’t worth it,"
    },
    {
      "index": 299,
      "start_time": 590329.0,
      "end_time": 593800.0,
      "text": "remember that this process led to the life that you have today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 300,
      "start_time": 593800.0,
      "end_time": 596889.0,
      "text": "one where I can teach you history through the magic of the Internet."
    },
    {
      "index": 301,
      "start_time": 596889.0,
      "end_time": 598709.0,
      "text": "Worth the sacrifices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 302,
      "start_time": 598709.0,
      "end_time": 599399.0,
      "text": "human and otherwise?"
    },
    {
      "index": 303,
      "start_time": 599399.0,
      "end_time": 601290.0,
      "text": "I don’t know. You tell me."
    },
    {
      "index": 304,
      "start_time": 601290.0,
      "end_time": 602249.0,
      "text": "Thanks for watching."
    },
    {
      "index": 305,
      "start_time": 602249.0,
      "end_time": 603310.0,
      "text": "See you next week."
    },
    {
      "index": 306,
      "start_time": 603310.0,
      "end_time": 604079.0,
      "text": "Crash Course is"
    },
    {
      "index": 307,
      "start_time": 604079.0,
      "end_time": 605300.0,
      "text": "produced and directed by Stan Muller."
    },
    {
      "index": 308,
      "start_time": 605300.0,
      "end_time": 606790.0,
      "text": "Our script supervisor is Danica Johnson."
    },
    {
      "index": 309,
      "start_time": 606790.0,
      "end_time": 607639.0,
      "text": "The show is written by"
    },
    {
      "index": 310,
      "start_time": 607639.0,
      "end_time": 610339.0,
      "text": "my high school history teacher Raoul Meyer and myself,"
    },
    {
      "index": 311,
      "start_time": 610339.0,
      "end_time": 612170.0,
      "text": "and our graphics team is Thought Bubble."
    },
    {
      "index": 312,
      "start_time": 612170.0,
      "end_time": 614290.0,
      "text": "Last week’s phrase of the week was “number four, letter u”"
    },
    {
      "index": 313,
      "start_time": 614290.0,
      "end_time": 616980.0,
      "text": "if you want to suggest future phrases of the week or guess at this week’s"
    },
    {
      "index": 314,
      "start_time": 616980.0,
      "end_time": 619389.0,
      "text": "you can do so in comments, where you can also ask questions"
    },
    {
      "index": 315,
      "start_time": 619389.0,
      "end_time": 621160.0,
      "text": "that will be answered by our team of historians."
    },
    {
      "index": 316,
      "start_time": 621160.0,
      "end_time": 622300.0,
      "text": "Thanks for watching Crash Course,"
    },
    {
      "index": 317,
      "start_time": 622300.0,
      "end_time": 623199.0,
      "text": "and as we say in my hometown,"
    },
    {
      "index": 318,
      "start_time": 623199.0,
      "end_time": 633199.0,
      "text": "Don’t Forget, You may be cool, but you’re no Neil DeGrasse Tyson."
    }
  ]
}